synthlab.api
Interface Module

All Known Implementing Classes:
BasicModule, BasicScriptModule, ModuleEnvelope, ModuleKeyboard, ModuleLFO, ModuleMixer, ModuleMultiplexer, ModuleOut, ModuleOutToFile, ModuleSequencer, ModuleVCA, ModuleVCF, ModuleVCO
public interface Module

This is the module interface. It represents an analog synthesizer module having input and output ports.

addInput

void addInput(Port input)
Add an input port to the module. This port will not be copied, but rather shared (i.e. you can modify it, but be sure to synchronize it beforehand)

Add input ports to the module. These ports will not be copied, but rather shared (i.e. you can modify them, but be sure to synchronize them beforehand)

clone

Module clone()
             throws java.lang.CloneNotSupportedException
This method should return a valid copy of the current module. All ports should also be copied (deep copy).

Throws:
java.lang.CloneNotSupportedException

compute

void compute()
This method is in charge of the actual computation of the module. That is, the module should read its input ports, and write to its output ports.
